name: r-labelled
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "2.9.1" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-labelled
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/labelled_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/labelled/labelled_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 9eb10b245f64f3fb7346121aa4cd98638946e1cc4208dd5e28791ef8fd62fa40

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr >=1.0.0
    - r-haven >=2.3.1
    - r-lifecycle
    - r-rlang
    - r-stringr
    - r-tidyr
    - r-vctrs
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr >=1.0.0
    - r-haven >=2.3.1
    - r-lifecycle
    - r-rlang
    - r-stringr
    - r-tidyr
    - r-vctrs

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('labelled')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('labelled')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/larmarange/labelled
  license: GPL-3.0-only
  summary: Work with labelled data imported from 'SPSS' or 'Stata' with 'haven' or 'foreign'. This package provides useful functions to deal with "haven_labelled" and "haven_labelled_spss" classes introduced by 'haven' package.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
